NOW IS THE TIME for us to act. The unions are fired up. They’re showing unwavering support for each others’ survival in this industry. The majority of our members would answer the call to stand side by side with the WGA in a strike to rightfully fight for what is fair for actors. 

I implore @sagaftra and the below national board members to champion a Strike Authorization Vote BEFORE we begin negotiations on June 7th. 

And fellow members: if you agree, please repost or share your own experiences and tag the below board members. OR email them directly at: governance@sagaftra.org, cc: serena.kung@sagaftra.org and write “ATTN: ALL National Board Members and Officers” in the subject. 

The guild represents you, the member and will only do what they think the members want. So let them know! They want to hear from you!

Sometimes I just sit down and start assembling things, and then when it’s finished, I’m like….oh god what have i done, haha.  This thing is heavy.  Like really big and really heavy.  Should i keep it or list in on Sunday?

Many other metal workers know this, so nothing new to see here….but for those curious, you can melt sterling spoons and forks and whatever else into more useful raw material called ingots, and then roll and form these little bricks into wire or sheet, depending on your design needs.

That glob of molten silver yesterday?  This is it now.  Gonna start making a bunch of these because i like wearing them, haha…the Cardiff heavy band.  I dig em…and I’ll crank out as many as i can between now and Sunday, when they’ll be available for everybody. : )

My shop is my happy place.  Nothing and no one here to make one feel like they are not enough, no judgement, no expectations….just a quiet, safe place to be creative and explore, away from the world, and hopefully earn a living.  This year, I’m going to start sharing from this space…I’ve been tidying things up and hopefully making them somewhat more presentable so i can begin filming here, and showing everyone a bit of what this space means to me, and what it does for me.  I have no idea how to handle technology, and am a bit of a dunce when it comes to social media, but I’ll be creating on YouTube and maybe TikTok, as well as IG, and hope you guys will tag along and hang out.  There’ll be some surf and moto stuff as well, when i can get help filming those things….I’ll make a more formal announcement when things are farther along and I actually have some content to share.  Happy Monday. : )
